f=Governance/board/custom/constitution-enforcement/SKILL.md · in=constitution-enforcement tests gated decisions against business's written constitution small set standing, near-immutable rules rules PASS, VIOLATION, UNCLEAR. skill carries enforcement *process* only; laws themselves per-business content operator writes template provided `assets/`). constitution exists until operator creates one, skill never invents articles fill gap. · p=Constitutions exist business's non-negotiable rules ("we never take debt above X," "we never sell user data," "no venture launches without named owner") get enforced consistently instead re-litigated whenever they're inconvenient. skill makes board reliable enforcement point: gated decision gets tested against applicable articles, ruling cites article, ambiguity escalated rather quietly interpreted away. · wu=Triggers: "constitutional review," "is allowed," "does violate our rules," automatically **first check** board's gate sequence whenever decision submitted governance review. for: judgment calls constitution doesn't cover (that's rest gate fiduciary-guard, risk-assessment-matrix, pre-mortem), drafting/amending constitution itself (operator's job; skill supply template flag ambiguities discovered use). · st:/ Protocol=`Load the constitution (configured path) \· -> If none exists: STOP — offer assets/constitution-template.md; nothing to enforce \· -> Identify which articles apply to this decision \· -> Test the decision against each applicable article, quoting it \· -> Rule per article: PASS / VIOLATION / UNCLEAR` · h3:Phase 1 — Load=Read constitution path board's config (`operational/agent/board-config.md`, `constitution_path`). path unset file doesn't exist, stop immediately: report constitution exists, offer `assets/constitution-template.md` starting structure, proceed enforcing rules never written fabrication. · h3:Phase 2 — Scope=List which articles plausibly apply decision under review, state applies (or rest don't). scoping shown output article silently skipped enforcement hole. · h3:Phase 3 — Test=applicable article: quote article verbatim, apply operational test (each article template carries one), state finding specific facts decision drive it. Findings article: · h3:Phase 3 — Test=**PASS** decision conflict article., **VIOLATION** decision conflicts. Cite article number exact conflicting element decision., **UNCLEAR** article's language doesn't clearly cover case. resolve ambiguity unilaterally; escalate (Phase 5). · h3:Phase Aggregate Ruling=Any **VIOLATION** overall ruling VIOLATION. **Non-negotiable:** constitutional violation cannot conditionally approved, mitigated around, waived board. paths forward (a) change decision, (b) operator amends constitution through amendment rule which board notes perform., violations, any **UNCLEAR** overall ruling UNCLEAR, escalated., PASS overall PASS; decision proceeds rest gate sequence (fiduciary-guard, risk-assessment-matrix, pre-mortem applicable). · h3:Phase Escalate Ambiguity=UNCLEAR goes operator with: article quoted, decision element cover, two readings tension. operator's resolution ideally become amendment clarification note constitution itself, ambiguity isn't escalated twice. · h3:Phase 6 — Log=Record ruling decision, articles tested, findings, overall ruling, date configured decision log (`decision_log_destination` board's config; operator directly until it's set). Rulings form precedent-like history; Governance department's precedent agent (Institutional Memory, built) eventual consumer. · of=`## Constitutional Review: [decision, one line] \·  \· **Constitution:** [file/version/date loaded] \·  \· ### Applicable Articles` · pr=**No constitution, enforcement.** Never invent, assume, "reasonably infer" article. empty constitution means skill reports exactly stops., **Violations negotiable gate.** Board can't waive constitution; operator's amendment process change it. Anything waivable belongs config thresholds (fiduciary-guard), constitution., **Quote, don't paraphrase.** finding cites article's actual text paraphrase interpretation drift starts., **Escalate ambiguity, don't absorb it.** UNCLEAR resolved silently board today becomes inconsistent precedent tomorrow., **Every ruling logged.** unlogged ruling didn't happen, can't serve precedent. · f=Config path unset file missing stop Phase offer template., Constitution exists operational tests (bare statements only) still enforce, flagging finding interpretation untested language, recommend operator add tests template's structure., Decision text vague test ask specific decision element(s) rather ruling summary., Decision log destination unset deliver ruling log operator directly say so. · b:with Other board Skills=Runs **first** gate sequence. VIOLATION ends review early fiduciary-guard, risk-assessment-matrix, pre-mortem don't run unconstitutional decision., fiduciary-guard owns *threshold* rules (spend, runway, ROI tunable business, waivable config); skill owns *categorical* rules (never-do's). rule keeps needing exceptions, belongs fiduciary-guard's config, constitution flag pattern seen., strategic-veto tests decisions against *locked strategy commitments* (which change quarterly-to-yearly); skill tests against *constitution* (which rarely change). shape, different document, different mutability., Boundary marcus: decision-critic improves proposal before it's submitted; skill part gate rules after.